race.comment: LONELY ONE (3) resumed three-and-a-half weeks ago over 900m at this track and was only beaten 1.2 lengths into fourth when doing her best work late. Fitter and will appreciate the rise to a winning trip. Leading player. REVOLUTION BELLE (7) progressed nicely last time out to finish just half a length from the winner in third over this trip at Balaklava. Best figures measure up. Sure to run well. DON'TCALLMECHAMP (13) was well fancied when resuming last start and proved too strong, scoring by a length over this journey at Wagga. Open to plenty of improvement and is expected to run well again. DEFICIT (2) turned in a decent effort last start to finish third over 900m at Murray Bridge. Looks to be in the right race so he should be in contention again.
